In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris discusses the January 6th Capitol hearings and the erosion of foundational aspects of the government and democracy. She emphasizes the importance of upholding rules, norms, and standards regardless of party affiliation. Harris expresses concern for the fragility of democracy and urges people to demand its integrity. Regarding the hearings, she notes that most of what has been covered was already known but perhaps not in as much detail. The conversation then shifts to the topic of abortion. Harris mentions convening constitutional scholars and faith leaders to discuss the potential impacts of a Roe v. Wade overturn. She highlights the broader implications for privacy rights, contraception access, and same-sex marriage. Harris emphasizes that the government should not have the power to dictate personal decisions and that individuals should be able to make choices in consultation with their religious leaders.